name Dampfnudeln with Plums
serves 16 pieces 4
note Alternative filling: apricots.
  <p>Goes well with cinnamon glaze, plum glaze or vanilla sauce.</p>
tags main, autumn, winter

# Yeast dough

- 300 g flour
- 0.5 tsp salt
- 2 tbsp sugar
- 20 g yeast
- 40 g butter, soft
- 150 ml milk
- 1 egg
Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Add the butter, milk and egg and knead into a soft, smooth
dough. Cover and leave to rise at room temperature for about 1 hour until doubled in size.
-> dough

# Preparation

- 16 plums
Halve and remove the stones.

- 150 g marzipan
Fill the plums with the marzipan.
-> filled plums

- 2 dl milk
- 3 tbsp sugar
- 30 g butter
@nodep
Warm the milk with the sugar and butter and stir well. Pour half into the prepared tin,
set the remaining glaze aside covered.
-> glaze

= dough
= filled plums
<p>Divide the dough into {16} equal portions and shape into balls. Flatten each ball,
place a filled plum on top, pull up the edges and press firmly together. Place the balls
seam-side down in the prepared tin. Cover and leave to rise for about 15 minutes.</p>
<p>Bake for 15 minutes in the lower half of the oven preheated to 180°C.</p>

- 3 tbsp flaked almonds
@ glaze
Increase the heat to 200°C, pour {.667} of the set-aside glaze over the Dampfnudeln,
scatter over the flaked almonds and bake for a further 15 minutes. Remove from the oven,
pour over the remaining glaze and serve immediately.
